Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery skyphos with start of turn to foot; interior glazed black; exterior: part of incised palmette and lotus festoon or cross with added red on lotus and on palmette petal.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 362, no. B473)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0345) (Phase 1)
